						<p>By using the Platform or Services, You agree that any legal remedy or liability that You seek to obtain for actions or omissions of other Members or other third parties will be limited to a claim against the particular Members or other third parties who caused You harm. You agree not to attempt to impose liability on or seek any legal remedy from Peer to Pier with respect to such actions or omissions. Accordingly, We encourage You to communicate directly with other Members on the Platform and Services regarding any participation requests or Listings made by You.</p>
						<h2>PARTICIPATION REQUESTS AND FINANCIAL TERMS</h2>
						<p><em>Participation Requests and Financial Terms for Hosts</em></p>
						<p>Hosts, not Peer to Pier, are solely responsible for honoring any BoatDay confirmations and making available any BoatDays listed through the Platform or Services, including Captained BoatDays. If You are a Host and participation in Your BoatDay is requested via the Platform and Services, You will be required to either confirm or reject the participation request within the Participation Request Period, otherwise the participation request will be automatically cancelled.  Failure to respond to participation requests within the Participation Request Period may have an adverse effect on Your rating as a Host on the Platform. When participation in Your BoatDay is requested via the Platform and Services, We will share with You (i) the first name and last initial of the Guest who has requested participation in Your BoatDay, (ii) a link to the Guest&rsquo;s BoatDay Account profile page, (iii) the amount of seats requested by the Guest for the BoatDay, (iv) the message (if any) included by the Guest along with such request, and (v) if You have linked Your BoatDay Account to an SNS (defined below) the names of any members of an SNS with whom You are &quot;friends&quot; or associated on the SNS if such individuals are also &quot;friends&quot; or associated with the Guest on such SNS, so that You can view such information before confirming or rejecting the BoatDay participation request. If You are unable to confirm or decide to reject a BoatDay participation request within the Participation Request Period, any amounts collected by Peer to Pier for the participation request will be refunded to the applicable Guest&rsquo;s credit card and any pre-authorization of such credit card will be released, if applicable. When You confirm participation requested by a Guest, Peer to Pier will send You an email, text message or message via the Platform confirming such request.</p>
						<p>If You owe or agree to pay any amount to Peer to Pier, whether as a result of Your participation in BoatDays, actions as a Guest or otherwise, then Peer to Pier may (but is not obliged to) withhold the amount owing to Peer to Pier from any payout amounts due to You as a Host, and use the withheld amount to setoff the amount owed by You to Peer to Pier. </p>
