						<h2>PAYMENTS & FEES</h2>
						<p><em>Key Terms</em></p>
						<p>&quot;Guest Fee&quot; means the additional dollar amount that Peer to Pier adds to the Contribution set by the Host, which is calculated as a percentage of the applicable Contribution. The Guest fee will be displayed to the Guest in the Application when requesting a seat onboard a BoatDay. </p>
						<p>&quot;Host Fee&quot; means the fee that Peer to Pier charges a Host for the use of its online platform, which is calculated as a percentage of the applicable Contribution. The Host Fee will be displayed to the Host when the Host creates a Listing and specifies the Contribution per Guest. </p>
						<p>&quot;Trust & Safety Fee&quot; means the fee that Peer to Pier charges a Guest per confirmed seat on board a BoatDay, to support the safety of and reliability between Members. The Trust & Safety Fee will be displayed to the Guest when the Guest is asked whether to send a BoatDay participation request to a Host. </p>
						<p>&quot;Fees&quot; means collectively the Host Fee, the Guest Fee and the Trust & Safety Fee.  </p>
						<p><em>Payments</em></p>
						<p>As a Guest, following participation in any BoatDay hosted by a Charter Host (a &quot;BoatDay Charter&quot;), you will automatically be charged the Contribution for that BoatDay. Notwithstanding the Contribution, the decision whether to make any additional payment in excess of the Contribution, and the final dollar amount of any additional payment You elect to make to a Host for participation in a BoatDay (the &quot;Tip&quot;) is at Your sole discretion, and the Host will not receive any compensation or consideration for Your participation in the BoatDay other than the amount (net of any applicable Fees) of the Contribution and the Tip. </p>
						<p>As a Guest, following participation in any BoatDay hosted by a Private Host (a &quot;Private BoatDay&quot;), You may elect to pay all or a portion of the Contribution to the Host for participation in such BoatDay. Notwithstanding the listed Contribution, the decision whether to make a payment, and the final dollar amount of any payment You elect to make to a Host for participation in a Private BoatDay, including any Tip (the &quot;Voluntary Contribution&quot;) is at Your sole discretion, and the Host will not receive any compensation or consideration for Your participation in the Private BoatDay other than the amount (net of any applicable Fees) of this Voluntary Contribution. You acknowledge and agree that failure by a Guest to specify the amount (if any) of Voluntary Contribution for a Private BoatDay within twenty four (24) hours following completion of such Private BoatDay, shall be treated by Peer to Pier as an election by Guest to pay the Contribution amount listed by the Host for the BoatDay, and Guest&rsquo;s credit card will automatically be charged such amount.  IT IS THE GUEST&rsquo;S SOLE RESPONSIBILITY, AND NOT THE RESPONSIBILITY OF PEER TO PIER, TO DECIDE WHETHER TO PAY THE CONTRIBUTION, OR HOW MUCH TO OTHERWISE CONTRIBUTE TO THE HOST.</p>
						<p>As a Private Host, You may receive from a Guest a Voluntary Contribution for participation in Your Private BoatDay. Each Host acknowledges that the decision to provide such Voluntary Contribution and the amount of the Voluntary Contribution, including any Tip, is at the Guest&rsquo;s sole discretion, and that other than specifying the Contribution for the purposes of creating a Listing, the Host will not request from Guests any compensation or consideration for allowing Guests to participate in a Private BoatDay, nor will the Host receive any compensation or consideration from Guests other than the amount (if any, net of applicable Fees) of the Voluntary Contribution.  A Voluntary Contribution may be any amount from $0 up, as elected by Guest.  </p>
						<p>The full amount of a Guest&rsquo;s Contribution or Voluntary Contribution (including applicable Fees and any Tip), will charged to a Guest&rsquo;s authorized credit card as follows: a) twenty four (24) hours following completion of a BoatDay Charter, b) immediately following completion of a Guest&rsquo;s specification and submission of a Voluntary Contribution for a Private BoatDay, or c) twenty four (24) hours following completion of a Private BoatDay for which a Guest has failed to specify and submit a Voluntary Contribution - and transferred (less the applicable Fees) to the Host.  All payments made are non-refundable. This no-refund policy shall apply at all times regardless of a Your decision to terminate usage of the Platform or Services, Our decision to terminate Your usage, disruption caused to Our Services either planned, accidental or intentional, or any other reason whatsoever.</p>
						<p>All Contributions, Voluntary Contributions, Tips and applicable Fees shall be facilitated through Stripe Inc. (“Stripe”) Peer-to-Pier&rsquo;s third-party payment processing service, and are subject to the <a href="https://stripe.com/connect/account-terms">Stripe Connected Account Agreement</a>, which includes the <a href="https://stripe.com/fi/terms">Stripe Terms of Service</a> (collectively, the “Stripe Services Agreement”). By agreeing to these Terms and Conditions or continuing to use the Platform, You agree to be bound by the Stripe Services Agreement, as the same may be modified by Stripe from time to time. As a condition of Your accepting payment processing services through Stripe, You agree to provide Us with accurate and complete information about You and, if applicable, Your business.</p>
						<p><em>Fees</em></p>
						<p>Peer to Pier receives the Host Fee, applicable as a percentage of each Contribution or Voluntary Contribution of more than $0 that a Guest makes to a Host for participation in a BoatDay, net of the Trust & Safety Fee. For the sake of clarity, the Host Fee is assessed on a Contribution after the assessment of the Trust & Safety Fee. Peer-to-Pier may change the Payment Fees as We deem necessary for Our business. We encourage You to check this Agreement and/or the Platform periodically if You are interested in keeping abreast of the rate of Our Payment Fees.</p>
						<p>Peer to Pier may change the Fees for Our Platform or Services, as We deem necessary for Our business. We encourage You to check this Agreement and/or the Platform periodically if You are interested in how We charge for the Platform and Services.</p>
